text:
hi, my name is roxanne darling (@roxannedarling) and this is my week to takeover instagram from the los angeles center of photography (lacp) @la_centerofphoto. i am an emerging artist currently living in santa fe, nm. i love that lacp welcomes out-of-state photographers to be part of their community. this week, let's talk about bodies, nature, and getting older!

image: 
i am: creating my future by occupying the present

the photos i’m sharing this week are of me, from my series of portraits in nature. as a 66-year-old woman and emerging artist, i’m exploring the:
* the natural desire to be unclothed outdoors, in the privacy of precious places;
* a newly discovered quality of self-acceptance for my aging self;
* an appetite to create art from the female gaze, as a type of reclaiming my time, my body, and my point of view.

the photos were taken in 2017-2018 on an extended rv trip around the western us with my partner. in many cases, the place itself spoke up first and invited me to explore ways of finding myself in nature. as a card-carrying member of the #metoo movement, i hope this work conveys a type of freedom of self-expression that is possible regardless of one’s painful past experiences.

the photos were shot using several cameras: iphone, dji drone, and a canon dslr. all images have been cropped square; some images have been slightly modified to meet instagram rules. *
*
*
#lacpinstagramtakeover #lacp #losangelescenterofphotography #lacpmember #lacenterofphoto #womenphotographers #picoftheday #iam #santafeartist #freethinker

text:
i wanted to take a moment to really introduce myself. 
my name is cora. 
i live in kingston on canada.
i have dealt with (and am dealing with)anxiety, ctpsd as well as an eating disorder (for 27years).
i love animals, especially when i can rescue them. 
i am a brand ambassador for ethereal&co (get 10% off with code cora10).
i recently have decided to volunteer with @girlsinclimestone .
coached gymnastics for over 20yrs and am working on launching an online lesson plan/programs business for coaches.
i have management and sales experience (4yrs) and despite my anxiety, deep down i like working with people in leadership roles. 
i love to write and have written resumes and cover letters for those struggling to get employment with their current one.

i manage a personal blog that follows my recovery from an e.d. and healing from cptsd due to childhood as well as adult trauma . it can be found by typing zemameyteypema followed by .wordpress.com . also, i have been featured by @nedic as well as @ethereal&co . 
i believe sharing my story gives those things less power and control over my life. also if even just one post i write helps even one person i believe it's worth it. when we share the pain it truly is easier to carry. it took me s lot to believe that, but it's true.

there is a lot more to me. i am looking forward to getting to know you as i follow you or you follow me. thank you for your support.

@thedailybeast reports: federal prosecutors in florida— including @realdonaldtrump current labor secretary #alexanderacosta—broke the law when they signed a secret plea agreement with billionaire #sexoffender #jeffreyepstein, a palm beach judge ruled thursday. 
u.s. district judge kenneth a. marra ruled that the decision to keep more than 30 of epstein’s accusers in the dark about the non-prosecution deal that allowed epstein, a prominent financier with #political connections, to avoid #federal #prosecution was #unconstitutional.

text:
a little ramble ahead. #mentalhealth #domesticviolence #911 #notperfect #deepthoughts #insidemyhead #abuse #metoo #partofme #mentalhealthawareness #domesticviolenceawareness #youneverknowsomeonesstruggle #bullying #gettingtoknowme 🖤🖤🖤🖤🖤🖤🖤🖤🖤 i know i'm not ugly but some days those dark thoughts filter in and no matter how much makeup or hairspray i have trouble shaking them. my elementary school years i was bullied, punched, pushed in mud, called an ugly b#@%& etc and generally treated like crap. my homelife until i was 10 was chaotic, abusive, neglectful, full of domestic violence. my first serious relationship as an adult he was cruel and prone to fits of rage. i walked on eggshells for almost 3 years. he would abandon me at malls and restaurants if we had an argument  when i had no license or funds to get home. he poked fun at my appearance and loved to point out my "huge nose" my weight gain even though he would guilt and push me into eating even if i wasnt hungry if he was eating. he even told me he loved to see me cry on several occasions.
📃📃📃📃📃📃📃📃📃📃📃 mind you this has been years ago, my husband is always supportive of me, tells me i am beautiful and takes pride in the fact i no longer apologize for everything or simply breathing.
 my husband is kind and funny and i love him very much. though some days these negative experiences creep in and make my mood sour and i have a hard time explaining to him why i feel this way. though these violences against me were terrible they do motivate me to be better, they inspire me working 911 and talking to citizens. they make me stronger and inspire me to let others in bad situations, domestic suicidal etc, know they don't deserve to be treated poorly. they deserve better and it can get better. 
during these bad days i have to focus on how much better life has gotten and how i can make a difference. i feel like holly golightly in breakfast at tiffany's, i get the mean reds. it's  hard to explain other than that to those around me. i'm not perfect but my imperfections make me try harder. 
#selfie #motd #self #childhood #relationship #goodwiththebad #inspired #howitick #ptsd #depression #progress
name: Jenni Z - Vintage Fangirl

. another side note- when i was making this i saw how easy it can be to photoshop out a little bit of someone’s waist, arm, etc. especially with society’s standards for body image and the ‘ideal body.’ ignore unrealistic expectations and try to appreciate the person you are. every body is beautiful, and no one is perfect. self love and care is so important.

text:
she’s different, this girl. you’ve known that from the second you laid eyes on her.

it’s the way she smiles, how it seems to stretch across her face like a child, innocent and unconscious.

it’s her laugh, and the way that it sneaks into conversation and makes the moment just a little brighter.

it’s the way she listens, with her eyes, staring into your soul, making you feel like you’ve known her all your life.

you can feel your heart slipping as the moment lingers.
she seems to know you like no one else does.
and that’s because she sees you, the real you, behind all your layers.

a girl with a big heart knows that the world is a flawed place. she’s had her fair share of pain and disappointment, but she’s chosen to turn her face to happiness, not negativity.

she’s chosen to wake up with a smile, chosen to see the light, chosen to find reasons to feel good, to bless others, and to live purposefully.

she’s always seen the world as big and scary, but believed that with small steps she could make it start to shine.

she has no problem reaching out to others, giving change to the homeless, offering to help the sick, opening the doors for people behind her, or smiling at strangers, just because.

she believes in the good, in forgiveness, in generosity, and in appreciating the small things.
she sees people as blessings and this life as beautiful. and she loves and loves and loves.

a girl with a big heart will change the way you see love.
see, she’s not afraid to give all of herself to someone. she’s not timid. she’s not guarded. instead, she opens. she trusts. she goes all in.

she sees people as opportunities for love, for connection, for relationships, for growth, for happiness.

and she loves because that’s what is inherent within her, to give to others and to put them first.

when you love a girl with a big heart, nothing before matters.

not the way you were treated, the past relationships that broke you, the trust that was crushed, the moments that left you feeling shattered.

all that matters is her arms, her embrace, her beautiful soul wanting to love you in the best way she can.

she will erase the pain from your mind and build new memories.

text:
perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,” from @backto_muslimidentity

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
follow along as we feature a woman of color on our story every day for the last week of #blackhistorymonth . 
although we should celebrate people of color every month, black history month is an opportunity for us to focus on how we treat minority groups in our culture. 
being an intersectional feminist means recognizing the challenges that come when multiple forms of oppression intersect. no two journeys through life are the same, and because of this we need to work harder to understand the struggles our fellow sisters and brothers experience.✊🏽💪🏿✌🏾

text:
sterilization:
indigenous women have experienced sterilization through different means. they either consented through being coerced or sterilized without their consent. sterilization is a safe birth control option for women, but it is abuse when it is used as an unauthorized procedure on marginalized women. indigenous women experience colonization and oppression in their lives and this is further applied on women’s bodies. indigenous women experience this injustice in their health systems as well; they are vulnerable to systematic abuse. health services make decisions on indigenous women’s behalf because they are experiencing oppression for being a marginalized group. indigenous women are also targeted because it is through them that they can reproduce the next generation of indigenous people that will fight against the colonial structure that is currently in place. the women who were sterilized did not speak out because of fearing of retaliation through a loss of being helped in the public health systems. protests and investigations began in the 1970’s that brought up how indigenous women were being sterilized without their consent or informed consent. informed consent would be a lack of understanding english doctors because their first(only) language would have been an indigenous language. futher, these women were misinformed from their doctors who did not explain sterilization to them or they may have been talked into it while they were anesthetized or were experiencing labour. many women did not remember signing forms because they were not fully conscious of their decisions. often the involuntary sterilization procedures were performed on indigenous women without medical cause. the hospital staff persuaded indigenous women because of their own perspectives of living a middle-upper class that indigenous women with lower socio-economic status could not provide their children with a decent life. .

article: the lost generation 
artist: unknown .
.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
today, i am reclaiming this song. this is one of many songs that my assaulter always played on the piano in high school. for years this song has brought back all of the pain, hurt, suffering and fear that i felt that day and for years after.  today it came on during my bath and i didn’t rush to hit skip. now, 7 years later to the day, i am reclaiming the music that was stolen from me. 
i am continuing to move forward, i am continuing to learn how to piece myself back together and i am learning how to love myself. there are days that suck. 
there are still moments when a guy will get too close to me at work or in public and i tense up, ready to fight back. there are still moment where i jump if someone comes up behind me without saying anything or touches my arm or shoulder and i have to take a deep breath and tell myself i’m safe.  there are still times when i cry about what happened, there are still times when i wish that i had done more to stop it from happening. but the past is the past, and i am fully committed to moving forward. fuck that guy, fuck what he did to me, and fuck it if i am going to let my fears control me. i am stronger than he will ever be, i am a tougher woman because of him, and i refuse to let him stand in front of my future. 
#metoo #sexualassault #isurvived #strongindependantwoman #ishallovercome

text:
things no one may have told you about healing from trauma...
🧐
🤷🏻‍♀️
you can get worse before you get better. this warning is in every therapist’s consent to treat (the stuff you have to sign before coming in for your first appointment), but it’s not talked about enough.
😱
🙄
you’ve probably exhausted most, if not all of your efforts in learning to cope on your own before coming into therapy. most of these efforts have not been adaptive or healthy. maybe you picked up an addiction or an eating disorder. maybe you have just been stuffing the feelings & thoughts that come up about it. maybe you disconnect or zone out as a way of dealing. maybe you get angry & rage at those you love as a way of letting off some steam. and, maybe it’s all not working anymore or they’re causing even more problems.
🤯
🙅🏻‍♀️
getting clean from these less adaptive coping mechanisms can be extremely difficult & there is loss & grieving in that too. replacing them with more adaptive skills can also be an uphill battle & then you add in patching up the old wounds & agh...! 🤬
🥵
healing from trauma is no easy task. you will go through ups & downs & sideways paths of growth. but, do not underestimate the work or the results... they’re both powerful is so many ways. 💯
🙌🏻
#elevate #notyourblankslatetherapist #trauma #traumatherapy #therapyhelps #growthisnotlinear #worsebeforeyougetbetter #ptsd #ptsi #cptsd #traumahealingisafight #battlewounds #metoo #startbybelieving #powerful

text:
my birthday is this saturday & though i don’t really celebrate it anymore, this years got me thinking about a ton of shit. i truly do wonder what 15 year old me would think if he met 35 year old me lol. .
.
i’ve just changed (like we all do) in so many ways. however, in so many other ways i’m still entirely the same person. that’s bittersweet to me, considering all the emotional baggage i’ve been carrying since childhood. i suppose i never acknowledged what being bullied as a kid did to my mind leading into my later stages of life. .
.
i’m a “daydreamer” to this day, same as i was as a kid. it makes me happy to know that even with all this fear and doubt i hold onto daily, that i have the courage to push past my fears, criticisms, and cynics with the ambition to achieve being something even greater than i ever dreamed back then. 📸 @photosbyfink

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytica $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
i’m shocked how many people think they’re alone in this...
even with social media and the #metoo and all these other feminist movements happening. you’re not alone!! heartbreak happens, shit things happen, but good things happen too. it’s a matter of mindset. you must change your habits to change your mind. and i get it, our habits are strong and after a relationship, shit they’re so much stronger. you’re used to doing so much with someone else. it’s literally like coming off a drug, all of a sudden you don’t know what to do with yourself. here’s the thing though, everyone used to say to me, “catie, it shouldn’t be this hard.” and no i guess it shouldn’t but i’m a fighter and i loved her so much and i’m stubborn as fuck so anytime someone said that to me all i wanted was to prove them wrong. i knew the love we had for each other was big. we had done shitty, shitty things to each other since the start. our relationship started with deceit, i don’t know if we ever trusted one another but we both kept fighting for each other and that to me at that time in my life was beautiful. i wanted to be fought for. i needed to know i was worth it, i needed that external validation. and it’s ok.
•
now, all i can say to you is look, no one but you can change you. you’re upset? you’re unhappy? you feel behind in life? fuck i’ve felt all those things but guess what, no one cares. no one cares as much as you do. so stop judging yourself. please. just start the journey. get better for yourself. why the fuck not? go put a mask on, exfoliate, moisturize, do some yoga, meditate, drink a smoothie, eat something green, just do something, anything and start to take care of yourself again. stop making excuses and certainly stop making excuses because of someone else... we’re all able to live the life we want. so start, put one foot in front of the other and know you’re not alone. 
from my 💚 to yours, xx.
•

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytica $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
✊✊🏾reclaim the night✊🏿✊🏻
when i was writing my dissertation recently, i focused partly on how protests have evolved since the birth of the internet and subsequently social media, and how this has improved movements by making them more accessible, giving them a larger audience and making it easier to educate people. but i think seeing everything through a screen can be a bit desensitising sometimes. it's never as passionate or feels as unifying as when you're surrounded by thousands of people all chanting until your voices go hoarse 📣 but if you want to do some good on the internet please sign the petition linked in my bio and help demand safer streets and an end to rape crisis cuts thank you ❤

text:
women finding the passion for jiu-jitsu and the feeling of empowerment it gives you!
.
in the last few weeks i have had more enquiries from women about how to get started in jiu-jitsu than from men
.
there has definitely been a shift in the interest of woman learning how to fight and defend themselves .
this does not always come from a bad place as you hear about so many times in the news. quite often the reason for starting to learn jiu-jitsu is the same reason as for men
.
the want to learn jiu-jitsu .

our woman’s only classes do allow a more relaxed transition into training.
it shows that jiu-jitsu doesn’t always need to be hard core and you can learn in a fun safe environment but still with an atmosphere of self empowerment .

don’t mess with these girls they’ll kick your ass!
.
come join in on a class
www.graciejiujitsu.com.au
.
.

text: abortion should’ve been legal since the beginning. i don’t get why pro lifers call those who get abortions murderers. would you rather have a child who is malnourished or depressed because their parents couldn’t afford food or adequate shelter? in additions, most abortions happen in the first trimester, when the fetus doesn’t feel anything. lastly, it’s their body, not yours. if you don’t support abortion, don’t get one. keep it to yourself.

text:
“are you signing your child up for lessons?” ~lady in waiting area. “um. hmm. nope. i’m signing myself up!!” ~ me

awkward silence followed by, “good for you.” and then i begin to “remember her” the tender hearted and fiercely brave little melissa ann. my answer to the kind lady could have easily been, “yes, i’m signing my child up for lessons. my sweet inner child who lost her voice years ago.” after being sexually assaulted i quickly learned it was best to keep my mouth shut. anything i said could and would be used against me in court. (and it was.) i was told my reputation would be ruined and others would judge me. my true self was only shared with a counselor behind closed doors. end. of. story! 
as my voice becomes more in tune with my truth i find myself longing for the parts of me i lost. including this singing star in the photo.  i mean really… check her out in the floppy hat and grandma’s pearls.

when the photo was taken i sang off key and my dress was three sizes too big. yet i still beamed with pride at the family talent show.

embarrassed by missed notes. nope!

oversized dress. who cares?

standing on a step aerobics platform instead of a stage. no problem!

recently, my voice has been called to get gently louder and the stage is beginning to get larger. i can’t think of anyone better to help me prepare than reconnecting with this brilliant girl. oh the things i can learn! 
so today i’m going to go get her!!! in all of her “feather boa” glory. honoring my fierce little melissa ann by taking an adult voice lesson.

please send the instructor love and patience 😂💕😂💕😂 #beher #findyourvoice
#metoo
#ibelievesurvivors #istandwithsurvivors #isupportsurvivors #littlegirlwithin #icansing #featherboa #musicforthewin #yourvoicematters #ihearyou #herecomesthechange #tbt #throwback #gogether

text:
on sunday, george mendonsa, the us sailor who kissed dental nurse greta friedman in times square on vj-day in that iconic end-of-wwii photo by alfred eisenstaedt, died. 
yesterday, the ‘unconditional surrender’ statue in florida depicting the photo was defaced with the words #metoo. 
what the f*ck is wrong with people? this is where our pc-crazed world is heading- to a place where war heroes are besmirched by virtue-signalling tossers, and where innocent joyful gestures are condemned as crimes. it’s sickening. rip george, and thank you for your service.

text:
“we, citizens and artists against animal cruelty, invite you to celebrate hollywood’s biggest and brightest night, in the fashion of compassion, by going fur free!
in 2019, no longer do we need to see senselessly tortured animals worn by humans on the red carpet, the oscar stage or on any other set, stage or screen. we now know that every fur coat or similar garment involves immense cruelty, such as the anal-electrocution or skinning alive of 30-40 beautiful animals, just for one coat. in a modern society, and especially in an industry that champions progressive values, equality and fair treatment for all (#metoo), there is really no place for such public displays of cruelty and total disregard for others, as we have recently seen at the super bowl half-time show, by one of the key performers.
as you may know, the city of los angeles has just banned the production and sale of fur, and is officially fur free (joining many other cities around the world) and the state of california has passed the california cruelty-free beauty products act.
we call upon you, moviemakers, artists, and trend-setters for the rest of the world, to join the ethical movement behind these laws, and display a cruelty free, fur free celebration of art, beauty and compassion on this magical night of the oscars!
“thank for signing and for sharing on all your social media platforms!” #furfreeoscars
thank you!

text:
#theorythursday notices that there are multiple narratives running through this multi-party scandal: 
1. khloe’s apparent curse of public, unending heartbreaks. 💔
2. tristan thompson’s documented, compulsive betrayals of the mother(s) of his children. 😬
3. jordyn’s tragic act of self-sabotage, which marks the end of an iconic friendship. 😿
what i’m noticing in the #media is an avid investment in the third story most of all: what this all means for #kylie and #jordyn. female friendship is one of the most powerful forces in the world, and this might be the greatest era for its societal recognition - between social media as a platform (at its best) to convey the beauty of sisterhoods, the ubiquity of a female-centered show like the #kardashians wherein men are fairly incidental, and even the unity among women brought about by #metoo. we’ve been seeing relational womanhood represented a bit more - and kylie and jordyn modeled a kind of closeness that felt true for anyone who has a #bff that feels like a #sister. the intimacy between them humanized kylie, who otherwise might sometimes be mistaken for a literal doll of kris jenner’s design. that jordyn lived with kylie also validated the high value of such a bond, normalizing the notion of chosen families. even the press doesn’t seem to be framing this with the standard (offensive and usually boring) #catfight narrative - there is some sense of genuine mourning in most subtext. 
my theory? the memes, jokes, and gossip about jordyn’s fatal mistake may be because witnessing the sudden end of a publicly authentic sisterhood has us feeling fucked up. i’m also inclined to theorize that this news is causing #shockwaves  because deep down, we can feel that it’s true - and are now digesting a rare incidence of real shit fed to us by a family whose elaborately strategic antics we’d become accustomed to accepting with suspended disbelief.
additionally, i suspect the hookup between jordyn and tristan may have been incited by a shared sense of alienation they experience amid the complicated kardashian world of constant engineering, but that’s another #theory for another #thurs

text:
😞he didn’t know he was actually being groomed, then sexually abused until he was actually abused.
.
🤫grooming allows sexual abuse offenders to have access to children, develop a 🤫secret and intimate relationship, then weeks, or either months later the relationship with them becomes sexual by touching, or non touching but still abusive.
.
😞many times children victims may not realize they have been abused because their body may have responded positively to the touch (most cases aren’t forced), or they weren’t actually touched but still abused.
.
📝preventative education will help empower your children to know when to tell, not to keep secrets, understand grooming, and stop the abuse before it begins.
.

#repost @melissadowler
・・・
when you run a business, every project is a chance to define who you are and what you stand for. i’m proud that @longhaulfilms, the production company i run with @tomdowler, has always been focused on elevating women in front of and behind the camera. after the impact of #metoo and #timesup, we will continue to challenge ourselves in terms of how we evolve as a company that embodies feminine values, and as creators of images that uplift, inspire and empower women. this video is a small selection of women we’ve collaborated with over the years. i share it to celebrate female forward filmmaking and to formally express my intention of working with many more women creators and innovators in the months ahead.

text:

we accomplish so much more than we often give ourselves credit for. so go ahead, start the list. and if you feel like sharing, drop a few accomplishments in the comments below. 😉

.
.
.
part 3 of my story: i started my second year of uni and was so motivated and things were going well. i hadn’t been out much because i had so much work but i decided to go out with with my friends. a decision i would regret for the rest of my life. i don’t want to go into too much detail because even thinking about it scares me. that night, just over a year ago, i was raped. but too be honest that wasn’t even the worst. when i tried to tell the security at the club they didn’t believe me. i was so scared and a mess, i was screaming and crying and i tried to kill myself. i was then sectioned under 316 of the mentally health act and woke up in a psychiatric hospital. after an assessment they let me go home, and it wasn’t until i got home that i realised what had happened to me. i was so scared, i didn’t know what to do. i called my mum the night after and she told me to call the police. the police came round and took my clothes and a statement. i had to go for forensic examinations and mediation to protect me from hiv. my mental health then deteriorated severely, i was regularly taking overdose and just wanted to be dead. 
but now just over a year on i am feeling so much better, i had intense group therapy and see a specialist sexual assault counsellor, which has helped so much. i still get flashbacks and the nightmares are bad, but i’m learning to cope with it and it has made me a stronger person. i will forever wish that night never happened but i’m proud of how far i have come since💪🏼🌼💛💛 #borderlinepersonalitydisorder #mentalhealth #bpd #suicideprevention #suicideawarness #mentalhealthawareness #recovery #positivity #follow #like #trauma #depression #anxiety #success #relationships #problemsolving #family  #relationshipproblems  #personalitydisorders #borderlinepd #therapy #help #helpingothers #lovingsomonewithbpd #recommended #mentalhealthquotes #itsokaynottobeokay #metoo #metoomovement  #therapy

text:
"the root of the harassment issue is actually inequality in employment," says leah meyerhoff, the founder of film fatales, a support group for female directors. "clearly when the majority of people in power are these able-bodied straight white men, a side effect is sexual harassment on set and in the world." of the top 100 grossing films of 2017, women represented 8% of directors; 10% of writers; 2% of cinematographers; 24% of producers and 14% of editors, according to the center for the study of women in television and film at san diego state university." read more at https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswglt

text:
to be who i am, a woman who rejoices in her {imago dei} femininity, has come with much pain. but i refuse to hate. i refuse to grow hardened. i will fight for my tenderness. i will fight for the value of women. i will challenge those who think women are small. to those who use us, only see us for what we offer in our beauty, our life-bearing, life-giving and life-making bodies (which should summon respect and honor on its own, yet we are not defined or limited to our bodies), i will continue to pray that you see the beloved treasure of the universe that is a woman. i will continue to pray that women whose worth has been trampled upon from the foot of man be lifted up out of the dirt and seen, empowered and that hope from the one who sees us and cares most deeply about us free us from the judgment and insecurities of one another and from those who are ignorant of our significance. 
i wrote a song about it. the link is in my bio on my artist account, @ll.funk ❤️ #woman #women #feminine #femininity #womanhood #womanempowerment #womenempowerment #imagodei #imageofgod #godisfeminineandmasculine #tenderness #beauty #divinefeminine #divine #value #worth #vocalist #sing #singer #songwriter #musician #music #metoo

text:
are you living a life true to yourself? and what does it even mean to be true to yourself?  for me it means listening to my soul. listening to that part of me that i can only hear when i slow down. when i allow myself to sit in silence, to be still enough to listen to what it wants me to know.  lately, when i do, the message is always the same “slow down sweetheart, spend time in nature, swim in the ocean, rest, nurture yourself”. “listen to your longings.” “you are exactly where you are meant to be. and so is everyone else”. i need to hear this (often!) as i can get so busy, doing, fixing, controlling, trying, striving – making it happen rather than letting it happen.  being true to myself has meant listening to my longings. my longing to leave my corporate career, to stop trying to be ‘successful’, to stop trying to earn my worth and justify my existence. to recognise i am already worthy, just being me. 
it means listening to my longing to write my book. to find my voice. to share myself, my story, my wisdom. what an incredibly vulnerable and courageous journey it is! 
it means listening for my longing for deep and authentic connection with myself and with others, and importantly, courageously, working through all the internal stories and behaviours that stop me living true to myself. my fears! 
it means listening to my longing to keep writing these posts and offering the authentic woman online program out into the world. our vision is to empower 1 million women to know themselves, care for themselves and be themselves. ultimately to live a life true to themselves. and this online program is a step-by-step path to do just that. and to live true to this vision we have decide to drop the price from usd $197 to aud $47 so more women can afford it.  we would love you to join us on this transformational journey. if you are interested check out our website link in the bio.
what do you long for? i would love to hear what being true to yourself feels like for you?
with much love
jo. and thanks to the wonderful @bronnie.ware for her book on the top regrets of the dying..this was their #1 regret!

text:
i haven’t taken my anxiety medication in weeks 🙌🏼✨
⠀⠀
this is a huge, gigantic win for me, and i want you to know, i’ve worked my 🍑 off to be able to say this. just because of this fact, this does not make my journey more successful or better than yours. it doesn’t make my life more shiny or beautiful, and this does not have to be your goal, just because of this fact in my life. got it babe? okay👌🏼 that being said, i do want to tell you the lifestyle changes i’ve made in order to shout this from the mountain tops with pride 💪🏼🏔 because this didn’t just happen. i still feel anxiety  e v e r y  d a y. i still have to fight with my brain, change the way i think, put effort into this journey. and i know you can do this. regardless if your goal is to get off your medication or not.
⠀⠀
1️⃣ i rest. like an obnoxious amount. i set time aside to be by myself, analyze how my day went. to journal, write down my goals, read posts that get my heart beating to create. i drink coffee in the mornings before going to work and i just sit. i leave space to be present and be.
⠀⠀
2️⃣ i see 2 chiropractors. it helps regulate our nervous system, and helps our body communicate effectively with itself. anxiety by definition is that there is a chemical imbalance in the brain. this means that functionally, something isn’t right in our body! girl, go find a chiropractor, like yesterday 🙌🏼💫
⠀⠀
3️⃣ i stopped taking hormonal birth control. i just learned this today, thanks to @whollyhealed and @rockyourbodpod — women who are on hormonal birth control are 24-36% more likely to be prescribed an anti-anxiety medication or antidepressant. i noticed a significant difference in my happiness, my feelings literally being let out of a box when i stopped taking the pill. done, next please 💁🏼‍♀️
⠀⠀
4️⃣ release stress. seriously, babes. stress knocks our body for a huge loop. it shuts off digestion, cell regeneration, immune support. cultivating a life free from stress is so so important. yes things come up — this week i crashed my car 🤷🏼‍♀️ know that you control your life. you decide what stays and what goes. be the gatekeeper of your life that you deserve 🙌🏼💓

text:
a violência contra as mulheres no mundo.

de forma geral, as regiões do planeta que menos garantem os direitos das mulheres continuam sendo a áfrica subsaariana, a ásia meridional e o oriente médio. mas tunísia, jordânia e líbano se destacam por seus avanços. na europa, o continente que mais pune a violência de gênero, a rússia se sobressai como o país menos seguro para elas. na união europeia (ue), a bulgária se destaca por não ter leis que criminalizem o estupro dentro do casamento e a hungria, por não punir o assédio sexual. em muitos outros países, especialmente na áfrica subsaariana e na ásia, o estupro não é punido se ocorrer dentro do casamento, o que deixa as mulheres desamparadas se o estuprador for o marido. destaca-se o caso da índia, onde, apesar da brecha jurídica, a suprema corte resolveu que o ato sexual será de fato considerado um estupro se ocorrer dentro do casamento, mas somente se a esposa for menor. 
#geo #geografia #bichogeografico #metoo #violenciacontramulher #world #maps #worldmap

text:
all of these boxes are untested rape kits. each individual box represents a person just like you and me. someone's child, parent, relative, friend, co-worker even neighbour. every box accounts for the girls and boys as well as both women and men who have been through the ordeal of a sexual assault. they then have found the courage to speak up and go through a violating and retraumatising process collecting evidence, just for it to be placed on shelves for days, weeks, months, even years. by keeping a backlog, we are telling survivors that what they've gone through isn't important, that their pain isn't validated and that in some way it is their fault.

it is time for change. it is time we stepped up, believe survivors and remove the guilt and shame that is so wrongly placed on them. we need to test these kits and all future kits straight away so that justice can be served.
@therealmariskahargitay 
#endthebacklog #iamevidence #mariskahargitay #joyfulheartfoundation #untestedrapekits #metoo #timeup #survivor #youmatter #ibelieveyou

reposted from @themusical_official - [이벤트] 💥2019 여성의 날💥을 기념해 <더뮤지컬>이 뮤지컬을 사랑하는 많은 여성 관객분들과 의미 있는 시간을 보내고자 특별 강좌를 마련했습니다. 이름하여 ‘뮤지컬 속 여성 돌아보기! (중고등학생 여러분 매우 환영
_
🗓일 시:  3월 9일(토) pm 6:00
📍장 소:  예술가의집 3층 다목적홀
💰수강료: 1만 원 ⠀⠀
_
신청 바로 가기 👉🏼 프로필 상단 링크 클릭 ⠀⠀
_
✔️ 강의 소개
공연계가 무대 안팎의 성평등을 이루기 위해 나아가야 할 방향은 무엇일까. 여성의 날을기념해 열리는 본 강의는 브로드웨이 뮤지컬 속남성 캐릭터와 여성 캐릭터가 어떻게 다른 차이를 갖는지 살펴보며 그동안 수동적이고 도구화된 존재로 그려져 온 여성상을 비판적인 시각에서 점검한다.
_
✔️ 강사 소개
극작가 겸 공연 칼럼니스트. 주요 작품에 <콩칠팔 새삼륙>과 <신과 함께 가라>가 있다. 최근 <더뮤지컬>에 ‘여성의 눈으로 본 2018 뮤지컬’, ‘브로드웨이와 웨스트엔드의 여성 창작자들’, ‘#metoo #withyou 그리고 musical’을 기고했다. 또한 네이버 올댓아트 필진으로 활동하고 있다.
_
#더뮤지컬
#여성의날
#특별강좌
#timesup 
#girlscandoanything - #regrann

text:
der weg zur gesellschaftlichen gleichstellung lädt noch. // wenn ich in die zukunft blicke bin ich zuversichtlich. durch mediale debatten wie #metoo wurden feministische themen gesellschaftlich sensibilisiert. es wird diskutiert. es wird über sexismus gesprochen. es wird zumindst darüber gesprochen. 
das beruhigt. das alleine reicht noch lange nicht aus aber ja, es beruhigt. 
mit meinem blick in die zukunft kommt aber auch ein mulmiges gefühl in meinem magen auf. 
es ist der rechtsruck. der rechtsruck in österreich, der rechtsruck in europa, ja auch der rechtsruck weltweit. und das bedeutet rückentwicklung. und rückentwicklung bedeutet wieder (noch) schlechtere lebensbedingungen für marginalisierte. und davor fürchte ich mich. darf man auch mal sagen, oder?

doch genau deswegen ist es wichtig, die eigene stimme zu nutzen. zu diskutieren, aufzuklären, sich zu informieren. und gemeinsam solidarisch zu sein. damit sich der rechtsruck entlädt und die gesellschaftliche gleichberechtigung wieder (noch mehr) nach vorne blicken kann.

macrotendencia 2020: multicultura. según la consultora wgsn:
《la dimensión multicultural se establece como un marco capaz de abarcarlo todo. ya hablemos de aspectos raciales, de género, religiosos o culturales, los nuevos protagonistas son lo que se denomina como las “nuevas mayorías”.
la hiper-conexión está permitiendo la sincronía de grupos que tratados en conjunto aparecen como una gran fuerza emergente y, ahora sí, imparable. movimientos como el #metoo, el despertar de la diáspora africana a través de películas record en taquilla como “black panther”, son algunos ejemplos actuales》.
las marcas deberán empezar a pensar en estas "nuevas mayorías"y comunicar estratégicamente. 
the future is now!

text:
let me tell you on thing.. despite of not being very keen on talking about myself and maybe not being the best writer or story teller, and for having a tendency of being a very introverted person in general, there is a story from the past years that i have had the need to verbalize for a long time (the story echoes a lot of things from my childhood as well). it is a story about falling both physically and mentally ill, exhaustion, shattered dreams, depression, ptsd, worry, being in the verge of death... but also about love, growing up, newly awakened dreams, success and finding your strength again with more strength that you thought was not possible to gain ever again.  a story about.. being alive. again.
would you listen to what i have to say? --- so, this is the quickly assembled haori-hakama-rose outfit i could possibly pull off  while being severely sleep deprived and somewhat hangover from the night before (yes, exactly, excuses, heh..). i was freezing to death so three shirts, two haoris, a hakama with two skirts and several scarves were necessary on that day. 
photocredits and thank you so for a fun day out to the most wonderful @dandy_offiziell
also, thank you @auroosaborealis for being the most wonderful friend at such difficult time in my life, and for giving my tired mind a chance to steam out the night before. <3 i very much so appreciate you all. <3

#haori #hakama #goth #isurvived #metoo

text: i have never loved anyone like i love big sur. my cloud 9 was only a few hundred feet above sea level amongst a library of redwood trees, my literature of answers left by the divine. moving from the sur indubitably remains a culture shock. as a survivor / womxn big sur was the only place i felt safe walking alone at night. never catcalled, i never had to worry about being prey. i didn't have to fear my vulnerability as another humans gain. i usually need someone to accompany me because of my fear of going out having clinical c- ptsd, making it impossible to feel safe as i felt i could never truly defend myself against new attackers. meanwhile monterey it was just me, the sea and the sound of the wild seducing my timid heart's hidden fervor. a transcendental calling that was louder than my fears... the magnetic pull of mountains redirected my anxiety. what a new thought - anxiety can be redirected, and i can be reprogrammed to be guided by my heart.. gaia. my distance from paradise is a daily heartbreak which lesson was to take big sur with me wherever i go. my move is a biblical portion of my life compromised of condors to whale sightings (which now has me looking for tattoo artists to commemorate my blessed walkabout). i fortunately survived and escaped horrific abuse with my dog, questioning my faith - but still the milky way tucked me in at night. the calla lily's guided me to the ocean from the river of my detachment. the animal kingdom facilitated the understanding of my place here (eco > ego). the twilight zone, ley line, divine force, area 51, lemurian temple-ridden, mermaid heaven haven.. big sur chooses its own and tests them vigorously, without mercy for your evolution of purity similar to the glistening dew at dusk. it succumbs you vulnerable as a winter storm, empowering you to clear the paths that do not serve you. inevitably we embark on the pursuit of a life of no sorrow. mine began at nepenthe, but it will start within myself. #nepenthe #stateofmind #bigsur #goddess #metoo

text:
the muses celebrate episode 100 by getting to know writer evelyn mcdonnell and discussing her latest book, women who rock: bessie to beyonce, girl groups to riot grrrl! women who rock features over 100 amazing artists and is written by a collective of incredible women. if that weren’t enough, each artist gets their own gorgeous illustration, all created by extremely talented female artists. one of our favourite additions to the book was a playlist suggestion to go along with each chapter. we read, we listened, we learned about old favourites and discovered new artists that are now in rotation on our own playlists. we simply cannot recommend this book enough and it was such a pleasure to discuss evelyn’s impressive career with her. oh and from this book has spawned a new activist collective called turn it up! which advocates for gender parity in the music industry including airplay, media coverage and employment. how kick ass is that?? you can purchase women who rock on amazon or where ever books are sold!

you can find evelyn on twitter at twitter.com/evelynmcdonnell & instagram @msladyevelyn

check out our network @rnrarchaeology for more amazing podcasts! ♡

text: today i am grateful to have the opportunity to inspire again. to encourage people to heal from past trauma and find their true self. instead of indulging in hate when things don't go your way and having to control of your environment at all times, i'm lucky to have the opportunity to encourage positivity even when shit happens. for anyone who knows my story, thank you for your support. for those in the same boat as me... you are not alone.. it's never your fault but it is your obligation to heal for the people you care about - so you can be a better person for them and the community. thank you the daily post for giving a the stage again to inspire. reach out, heal and let your true self shine 😘 #metoo

text:
siden december er der kommet 400 nye venner ind på siden, så her er en ultra-kort intro af mig, præsenteret på fornemmeste vis med en “10 ting du ikke vidste om mig”
💙
1. jeg er faktisk ret skæg, men prøver at holde det under kontrol, fordi, du ved...jeg er parterapeut. så folk må gerne kunne tage mig en lille smule seriøst.
.
2. jævnfør punkt 1 kan jeg henvise til mit alterego @anjanynnemusic .
.
.

3. jeg buster myter om parforhold og sex, og bringer sandheder på bordet fra min praksis
.
4. jeg laver andet end at være på instagram. jeg tager også imod klienter i min praksis i lyngby
.
5. jeg fortæller også en smule om livet som selvstændig, og fortæller ærligt om, at jeg stadig supplerer op med 10 timer om ugen som aflaster .
.
6. jeg blev egentligt forlovet sidste år, men der gik noget galt med nem-id, så det har vi ikke lige fået gjort mere ved
.
7. min barndom var utryg og ikke særlig børnevenlig. min mor er narcissist og jeg arbejder med par, hvor fortiden spænder ben
.
.
8. jeg drømmer om at få mit eget radioprogram på @drp3
.
.
9. jeg har lige fået lavet permanent makeup på mine øjenbryn, og jeg elsker det!
.
10. jeg er kæmpe fan af #metoo og går virkelig meget op i at bekæmpe hverdagssexisme. se blandt andet min story i dag, hvor jeg taler om, hvordan ord og formuleringer har magt
.
thats all... noget du vil vide?
#10ommig

text:
when i left my abuser, i knew i wanted to help other victims... i made the decision to reach out to my local domestic violence shelter to see if i could volunteer. i started by working the front desk, and that soon evolved into me telling my story (for the first time ever) at their annual vigil, leading community outreach efforts, and even working for them! i never imagined that this would mark the early days of my future studies, career, and business.

takeaway: if you’re passionate about something, make that thing your mission. commit to it, even in a small way. just start. all it takes is doing a little research and asking how you can help. you never know how far it might propel, transform, and inspire you. 💫💜

according to the dailyhunt
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."
-

according to the dailyhunt
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
women supporting women. now. today. always. i got your back. 💪
•
growing up i was a “guys” girl. i grew up in a neighborhood with 7 boys, inherited 4 step brothers, and would rather listen to #metallica than n’sync. i just got along better with guys. there was less drama, jealousy, and at the time they seemed funnier. 😏
•
but becoming an adult has changed that immensely. women have become my best friends. i have found connection and strength (especially since becoming a mother) in the challenges we face as females. my girls know what it’s like to sacrifice your body, career, time to have a baby, what it’s like to be sexually harassed/assaulted, the stereotypes we face as artists and in life, and the power of a great mascara.
•
there are just some things the dudes can’t understand. and all that we share as women should be used to unite us, not to tear us apart. when i see a strong woman i want to know her, i want to surround myself with her, learn her secrets, not tear her down. we always have the choice to either be #intimidated or #inspired by those who are what we long to be. i choose inspiration.
•
for more badass #femalepower check out www.florencegiven.com and buy a mf badass bitchin t-shirt. (not sponsored, just inspired)
•

text:
today i had the opportunity to speak to hundreds of students at iowa state. what stood out to me the most was my conversation with a student who was the boyfriend to a sexual assault survivor. ——— he told me how upset he was after his girlfriend told him she was assaulted by someone they both know. even though it happened a while ago, he was so aware of her pain and how it impacted her.

________

he handed me his phone and shared the bravest message i’ve ever seen. he texted the perpetrator (who he knew) and let him know how horrible he was to sexually assault someone. he let him know that he didn’t care about his reputation or fraternity perception because it was nothing in comparison to the toll it’s taken on his girlfriend. he made it clear how wrong he was and even share the definition of sexual assault. 
______

i felt the anger and sadness he had and his feelings of powerlessness. i’ll never forget the look in his eyes. i imagine that he sits everyday in what feels like a mess, sorting through his own feelings about this and his responsibility as a boyfriend. i think about the mess that this woman is sitting in and sorting through. i don’t know if there will be criminal penalties against this perpetrator, but i do know that someone has held him accountable in the bravest and boldest way. i hope that he thinks twice the next time he decides to sexually assault someone. 
_______

if you’re reading this, i see you and feel you. sending you healing thoughts. the perpetrator never texted him back. #sexualassault #sexualviolence #metoo

text:
written by emma goldberg for @washingtonpost ”the tech industry’s male bent was by no means preordained. the group of programmers selected to work on the u.s. military’s first computer in 1946 was more than 50 percent women. one of the most celebrated early engineers was grace hopper, a navy admiral whose programming enabled the united states to model the impact of atomic bombs. it was also a woman, margaret hamilton, who led the coding team that charted apollo 11’s path to the moon. the conditions were far from glamorous, but the female programmers were known for their meticulous work ethic and attention to detail: hopper famously identified the first-ever computer “bug,” tracing a glitch back to a moth trapped in a relay wire.” #metoo #metoomovement #womeninfilm #kickasswomen

text:
six years in and the urge to purge continues. ive been sorting and dumping all types paper for 3 days now.  over 40 years of photos, cards , letters, stickers, newspaper clippings and post cards. today's treasures include:  a #pinkfloyd album poster and a #wonderwoman poster , my 20 yr old sticker collection with #gratefuldead stickers and #shambhala stickers from 2003 -2009 ,  postcard collection with #vintagepostcards from #nelsonbc, a  #nelsondailynews with my doggo making the cover, my first piece of "art" that ive had all mer life #jesuslovesme 🐼 ,  and last but certainly not least a stash of documents,  photos and police tapes from a court case involving an art teacher in my highschool in the 1990's including letters, cards and tapes from the predator himself. i know im not the only person affected by this type of business , it went on from 1978- 1997 and 17 of us came out once the abuse  eventually came to the surface. so many people in power knew it was going on for years and to that i say shame on all of you.  #elliotlakesecondaryschool #shameonelss #shameonyou #gregshafley ? #metoo #canadianartist  #blindriverontairo #ifyouknowyouknow but for real, more people should know. #googlethatshit

one of my 2019 goals was to move toward speaking my mind more. although im pretty open about my experiences, i wasnt going to share  revisiting the trauma from my time spent at elliot lake secondary school and greg shafley today.  but goals is goals and ive spent over 20 yrs protecting him (and myself and my family to some degree) so im done doing that. ✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨ #wedorecover #recovery #recoveryispossible #themoreyouknow ! 😉  as kiss would say #shoutitoutloud #gratitude
name: Public Figure- Dj Boo sent me

text:
gather round family||it’s story time💫
****************************************************** once upon a time, i asked god to save me from myself
so he pulled me close and wrapped my ears around my heart “listen,” he said
in that moment i was still
crippled in the questioning of my own existence 
i could feel the ground shifting from under me
but i knew then, no matter how much it hurt
he’d never let me go.
#zewidituisms 📷 @jicasso_stylez

text:
according to study done by #medscape in 2018, 50% of female physicians stated they had experienced some form of harassment by a patient. as medical student we are exposed to a world where there are always people over us , by this we mean residents, attendings, etc. there may be situations in which due to their power an environment of harassment  may be seen and many students  maintain silence because “their grade depends on it”. this is not acceptable and we must speak out! 🗣the #metoo movement has been creating awareness about sexual harassment and at sjb we decided to unite to this movement and let others know that you are not alone. at sjb we stand be you! 💪🏻
.
.
.
.
#metoomovement #metoo #medicalstudents #sjb #usmle #medicalschool #awarness #femaleempowerment #gogirl #nomeansno #puertorico #speakup #youarenotalone #jointhemovement

text:
i am a person. i am a woman. i’m small and dainty. i enjoy paint on my nails and a good song on the radio. im clumsy. i’m funny. i’m smart. i care. i love. i give and keep giving. i just need to learn when giving is to much. when to give to others and when to give to myself. every day my life has challenges. i struggle with mental health. ptsd, anxiety, and depression. i dream of the bad guys while i’m sleeping and fight to look for better days when i wake up. most importantly i’m a survivor. i don’t live in fear anymore of those who have hurt me. i’m growing. i’m changing. i’m a sunflower. i’m  art. i carry my head high and push forward. i let you know you are not alone. i’ve been there. that’s just a part of me now and it doesn’t define who i am anymore then being lazy or singing in the shower. don’t let your demons win. don’t let them mold you. embrace you. 
one : it’s not your fault
two:you will get through this
three: there will come a day you don’t think of it. 
four: you will heal. a scar will remain but you will heal. 
for anyone who has suffered or is suffering domestic violence, sexual violence, or abuse of any sort then message me 
or call 1- 800-799-7233 for the domestic violence hotline
1-800-656-4673 for the sexual assault hotline

remember you are strong and you are not alone💕

photography @d.culpepper 
#mentalhealthawareness #mentalillness #photography#strong#brave#fight#ptsd#anxiety#depression#assault#domesticviolence#domesticabuse#metoo#heal#health#growth

text:
un mot sur #lagerfeld ! 
je ne vais pas être longue... quand je vois tous les gens qui te rendent hommage, ça me rend un « tantinet »furax ! 
je rappelle que ta carrière, karl, a été alimentée de réflexions sexistes, grossophobes et pathétiquement misogynes. 
karl, tu plébiscitais la maigreur extrême, tu as dénigré #metoo, et tu cultivais énormément d’aigreur sur les féministes. 
en réalité, karl t’étais le roi du mauvais goût, un maestro du « #bodyshaming », un homme condescendant et méprisant que je n’ai jamais aimé. 
pas de place pour toi dans mon #panthéon, j’espère que le monde de la mode te remplacera vite, avec d’autres corps, d’autres silhouettes et remplira le vide que tu as laissé, par de la bienveillance et de l’humanité. 
en attendant je vais me resservir des chips, assise, sur mon gros cul de moche !

text:
27 years ago today (2/21/92), a dream became reality. i took the stage for the first time. i was a bundle of nerves, but i got laughs (and took 2nd place at my school's #apollo night). 3 years later, i did my 1st tv show (#defcomedyjam) that aired close to my 4 year comedy anniversary (2/16/96). last night @mikeyardcomedy & i reminisced on taping #defjam. @vondecarlo was tryna interrupt headliner talk, but we kept it moving. mike was surprised that i remembered his #chickenfish bit, but one of the dope things about doing #dcj was how e'rybody that did the show had at least a few memorable bits. #comedyquotables
@affioncrockett was the 1st kat i ever saw do a #berniemac impression & the only comic to dance at the end of the show during the credits. @rudyrush had the bootleg movie bit and messing with his mother's friend joke. @corey_holcomb's 2 faucets in 1 sink bit. i had the @tyrese #cocacola opener (2nd picture) & the #aaronneville jawn with a few rappers (#craigmack #odb @llcoolj) in between. i was in a good class of talent. thanks @bob.sumner for booking us and for e'ryone that has or does support comedy.
fame is fleeting and the current state reminds us that fame for fame's sake should not be the goal. one's hard work behind their talent reaps the reward of success in various forms. focus on your gifts and hone your skills. #beundeniable & prepared for your opportunity so that when it finally comes, you're ready. ok, i ramble. lemme go write this fart joke to maintain balance.
it is a marathon, y'all. 
27 years. woof! and we're still in it. #salute all the artists out'chea grindin'. i see your vision. #keepshining🌟
#blackdontcrack #totwats
#futhamuckinfunny

text:
the topic that makes everyone uncomfortable and happens far more frequently than spoken about.... "sexual assault"
.
in my empowerment memoir, "live through it..." i speak about being silenced for over 20+ years regarding being sexually violated at the age of 9 years old. after starting my healing from the inside out... i made a vow to never be silenced again... and when given the opportunity...to shed light on sexual assault in all capacities in an effort to encourage more victims to find their voice- i would!!!.
im grateful for additional organizations who have made it their mission to speak out against these  acts that are life altering and shattering to the victims!! join me in my effort to raise money while bringing awareness to sexual assault at the annual teal walk!! i have registered as a team captain in addition to being a vendor within the park where i will be selling on hand copies of "live through it...". if you are interested in joining me for this amazing event.... please inbox me for additional details ❤💪🏾🙏

let me start by thanking jussie smollett for abusing his freedom and ruining black history month at one of the worst times in history & for not only making a fool of black people; but also victims of: sexual, violent, physical & verbal assault, lgbt,  aswell as immigrants! 💩 #donkeyoftheday

real #empowerment
when i met my husband, i was wearing a suit...on our first date, i did the opposite of what women typically do, i am known for my heels, but i intentionally wore unflattering flats and my least "sexy" jeans, my hair was up in a bun... i was not wearing make-up ...i needed him to see the real me because i had learned to value myself and i knew that if he couldn't value the real me, he wasn't for me.

text:
* börja med dig själv *⁣⁣
vi är alla med och bidrar till destruktiva normer genom vad vi gör eller inte gör. kanske har du sagt eller gjort något som gått över gränsen, eller så har du inte sagt eller gjort något när andra gått över gränsen? att börja med sig själv tror jag därför är en väldigt bra väg om du vill vara med och bidra till förändring.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
det finns massor av sätt att arbeta med sig själv, och som en viktig del i mixen vill jag varmt rekommendera att gå med i (eller starta) en samtalsgrupp genom föreningen mäns (@manforjamstalldhet) samtalsrörelse #eftermetoo. samtalsformen innebär att gruppen tillsammans skapar en trygg miljö där alla pratar och reflekterar utifrån sig själva om förbestämda frågeställningar som berör bl.a. mansnormer, sexism, #metoo, hur vi är och hur vi vill vara. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
jag har under det senaste 1,5 året deltagit i två samtalsgrupper. det har varit och är fortfarande tungt, omvälvande och nedbrytande, men också stärkande, lärorikt och helt fantastiskt kärleksfullt. jag har upplevt att deltagarna kommer dit med väldigt olika bakgrund, erfarenhet och tankar, samtidigt som det finns massor och åter massor med igenkänning. i båda grupperna har det blivit mycket förtroliga och starka samtal trots (eller pga) att vi inte känt varandra tidigare.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
utmaning: steget från att läsa det här inlägget till att faktiskt söka sig till en samtalsgrupp kan kännas stort, och förmodligen ganska läskigt (det gjorde det i alla fall för mig). men jag hoppas verkligen du antar utmaningen - det kommer att vara värt det! på mäns hemsida (se länklista i bio) finns information om befintliga lokalgrupper du kan söka dig till på din ort. finns det ingen lokalgrupp så går det bra att starta en samtalsgrupp ändå - och även det hittar du mer information om hos män. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
jag är involverad i lokalgruppen män västerås, så om du är nyfiken får du gärna kommentera eller skicka dm. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
du hittar även länkar till andra initiativ om att "börja med dig själv" i länklistan i bio. har du fler tips för hur vi kan arbeta med oss själva, får du gärna dela med dig kommentarerna.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#börjameddigsjälv #jämställdhet #normer #mansnormer #manlighet #machokultur #feminist

text:
setiap orang berhak mendapatkan rasa aman atas bentuk tubuh dan ekspresi gender, begitu pula dengan cara berpakaian dan ekspresi tubuh yang lain. oleh karenanya pelabelan negatif seperti gambar diatas merupakan bentuk pelecehan seksual.

tidak ada "perempuan nakal, binal, bispak, sundal"!! dalam lingkungan masyarakat yang masih patriarkis, kita sering mendengar pelabelan negatif (stereotype) tersebut. perempuan yang mendapat stereotip seperti ini lebih rentan terhadap tindak pelecehan, karena masyarakat sendiri bahkan membenarkan tindak pelecehan terhadap perempuan yang mereka labeli demikian.

stereotype tersebut salah dan tidak dapat dijadikan landasan bagi siapapun untuk membenarkan tindak pelecehan seksual terhadap orang lain. label "perempuan baik-baik" ataupun "nakal, binal, bispak, sundal" adalah cerminan konstruksi sosial yang tidak setara, merupakan bentuk penghakiman moral dan kontrol terhadap tubuh perempuan.

text_retweet:
bye karl ✌️allez voir le post original de @tasjoui pour plus de détails ! 🔶🔶 #repost @tasjoui ・・・
✔️faire des hommages à karl lagerfeld ne devrait pas se faire sans que ce soit l’occasion de remettre en question le monde de la mode et du luxe et de mesurer l’impact toxique et néfaste des valeurs de cette industrie sur les femmes.
✔️ sa mort devrait être une célébration de l’espace qu’il laisse de libre ! c’est l’occasion de célébrer des talents plus éthiques qui aiment véritablement les femmes. l’occasion de célébrer d’autres types de corps. l’occasion de créer une mode aux valeurs éco-féministes. l’occasion de se demander si ce modèle de starification d’un « designer star » a encore du sens, lorsqu’il s’agit derrière lui, d’énormes équipes d’ouvriers. l’occasion de se demander si le modèle des défilés grandiloquents de chanel ou d’autres marques de luxe, où énormément de ressources et de matériaux sont utilisés pour quelques minutes de défilés ont encore un sens dans un monde où l’urgence est de consommer moins. 👋 allez ciao karl, t’inquiètes pas, les femmes se réveillent, tu nous manqueras pas.✔️🤯 pour ceux qui ont du mal à comprendre pourquoi je parle de ça ici: 1/ @tasjoui est avant tout une page féministe et activiste qui parle de sexualité et d’intimité comme le dernier bastion d’une bataille pour l’égalité. 2/ quand l’image du corps de la femme est salit par les industries de la pub, mode etc, la sexualité des femmes en prend un coup aussi, les femmes ont une vision distordue de leurs corps et par conséquent sont mal à l’aise avec elles mêmes. les hommes ont des attentes corporelles irréalistes etc. 3/ @tasjoui propose une vision à 360 degré du problème et ne parlera jamais que de sexualité, mais de tout ce qui fait que la sexualité, peut par effet crescendo être compliquée pour les femmes.
#fashion #karllagerfeld #sexist #chanel #racist #metoo #luxe #sorrynotsorry #fashionblogger

text:
what lies behind us and what lies before us are tiny matters compared to what lies within us. - ralph waldo emerson 
today i woke up anxious, hands shaking, sweaty, it was hard to breathe, my muscles felt like they were all cramping at one time. anxiety and ptsd are not fun. however, this too shall pass. this quote helps make me think a little bit better of myself. i have a lot of good within and in moments like these i need a little reminder of that. i’m using this pic as the one to express my feelings today because i am raising a woman who watches me go through these emotions and sees her momma is not perfect but loves me anyway and in these times where i think i am not good enough she shows that sweet smile and everything melts away. 💕 #dvsurvivor #anxiety #mentalhealthawareness #momlife #youtube #life #real #honesty #influencer #mom #metoo #mystory #selfaware #quotes #wisewords #anxious #ptsd #onedayatatime #thistooshallpass

february 21 2019  by patrice lee onwuka  a statue commemorating of the iconic moment when an american sailor kissed a random woman to cheer the surrender of japan, was vandalized recently because some now consider it a celebration of crime not triumph. in the era of #metoo, no stone is being left unturned. you probably know the “kissing sailor” photograph taken in new york city in 1945. a jubilant 26-year-old sailor, george mendonsa, grabbed and kissed 21-year-old greta friedman. the moment was captured on camera and, subsequently, became the symbol of the war’s end. sarasota, fl installed a statue depicting the moment over a decade ago, but after mendonsa passed this weekend at age 95, someone spray painted the statue with “metoo.” the reactions from feminists and leftists appears to be that doing wrong can be excused because the original moment was a crime. as one woman explains: “some think of the tagging as a desecration but it really highlights the prevalence and neutralization of sexual assault and rape culture. grabbing friedman and kissing her without her consent was wrong 70 years ago and it is wrong today.” they feel justified by friedman’s description of that the…
